#: ../../../admin-guide/vga-softcursor.rst:7
msgid ""
"Linux now has some ability to manipulate cursor appearance.  Normally, you "
"can set the size of hardware cursor.  You can now play a few new tricks: you "
"can make your cursor look like a non-blinking red block, make it inverse "
"background of the character it's over or to highlight that character and "
"still choose whether the original hardware cursor should remain visible or "
"not.  There may be other things I have never thought of."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/vga-softcursor.rst:15
msgid ""
"The cursor appearance is controlled by a ``<ESC>[?1;2;3c`` escape sequence "
"where 1, 2 and 3 are parameters described below. If you omit any of them, "
"they will default to zeroes."
msgstr ""

