#: ../../../admin-guide/vga-softcursor.rst:35
msgid ""
"selects character attribute bits you want to change (by simply XORing them "
"with the value of this parameter). On standard VGA, the high four bits "
"specify background and the low four the foreground. In both groups, low "
"three bits set color (as in normal color codes used by the console) and the "
"most significant one turns on highlight (or sometimes blinking -- it depends "
"on the configuration of your VGA)."
